  m_Name: Question-18
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Question
  HeaderLine: Which of the following best describes the role of FLOT in resectable
    gastric/GEJ adenocarcinoma?
  AsnwerSlot:
  - ) It is used only in metastatic disease
  - ) It is a perioperative regimen used for appropriate resectable patients
  - It is indicated only after recurrence
  - It is a radiotherapy sensitizer rather than a systemic regimen
  IsCorrectAnswer: 00010000
  Reference: 'Reference: Al-Batran SE, Homann N, Pauligk C, et al. Perioperative
    chemotherapy with fluorouracil plus leucovorin, oxaliplatin, and docetaxel versus
    fluorouracil or capecitabine plus cisplatin and epirubicin for locally advanced,
    resectable gastric or gastro-oesophageal junction adenocarcinoma (FLOT4). Lancet.
    2019;393(10184):1948-1957. '
